<p>I wish make working with public CouchDB database only via <strong>_rewrite</strong> I add string to <em>local.ini</em> to <em>vhosts</em>:</p>  <pre><code>*/mydb = /mydb/_design/doc/_rewrite </code></pre>  <p>It's working good, all requests to <em><a href="http://localhost:5984/mydb" rel="nofollow">http://localhost:5984/mydb</a></em> redirect to <em>_rewrite</em></p>  <p>But I can't make this vhosts rule via futon, or via curl. Futon return me error in jquery.couch.js. </p>  <p>I dont know how make this curl valid:</p>  <pre><code>curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \         -X PUT http://127.0.0.1:5984/_config/vhosts/*/mydb \         -d '{"/mydb/_design/doc/_rewrite"}' </code></pre>